data.TAXON_REMARKS: erroneously in NCBI as Anemone pulsatilla, correctly known as Pulsatilla vulgaris. The expanded concept of Anemone is based on a flawed study from the 1990s where Clematis was used as outgroup when it forms the ingroup of Anemoneae. If Anemone is accepted in this broadened concept including Pulsatilla and Hepatica, it will also need to include Clematis to prevent paraphyly. This has been published but is not picked up by NCBI
